post_text: All students in the Okaw Valley School District will now be eligible to receive free meals through December 2020. This applies to students attending school in-person, and those attending remote learning. This is made possible by the extension of the Summer Food Service Program (SFSP) - a federally funded , state administered program that provides reimbursement from the U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA) for any free meal served to a child age 18 and under. There is no paperwork needed from parents. All remote learners who are interested must contact their building in which they attend.

Okaw Valley CUSD #302 Reopening Plan 2020-2021

We thank everyone for their patience and support during this time. The only thing that seems to be certain in today’s world is uncertainty. Our goal is to provide a sense of normalcy to our students, staff, and families come August. Please take the time to register online at www.okawvalley.org.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1MvY5IwZH7MoVM5bahwAeTDuwsP0mFGnG/view?usp=sharing

In-person registration will take place on August 6th at Okaw Valley High School from 11:00 am to 7:00 pm, and August 7th at Okaw Valley Middle School from 11:00 am to 4:00 pm.

post_text:
Thank you to everyone who played a part in today’s 2020 graduation. This was no small task to execute and it went very well. Thank you to the class of 2020, your parents, and families for their patience and understanding throughout the end of this school year. The day was special for the kids and families and we are so grateful to have such a strong community.

Thank you to Bethany Sales for donating the fireworks that kicked off the parade with a bang!

Lastly, thank you to the entire Okaw Valley community for showing up at the parade today. It meant the world to our kids. We have a special community that continues to grow and come together in success and times of need.

The future is bright for our kids and community. Thank you and let’s continue to come together and stay strong. #YNotOV
